Class Classified

java.lang.Object
Earthquake
Classified
All Implemented Interfaces:
Comparable<Earthquake>
public class Classified extends Earthquake
Classified is a subclass of Earthquake that represents a classified earthquake event with additional information about its magnitude classification.

  • Constructor Details

    • Classified

      public Classified(String dateTimeZ, double latitude, double longitude, double magnitude, String id, String place, int lineCounter)
      Constructs a Classified earthquake object with the specified attributes.
      Parameters:
      dateTimeZ - The date and time of the earthquake in the format "yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ss.SSS'Z'".
      latitude - The latitude of the earthquake's location.
      longitude - The longitude of the earthquake's location.
      magnitude - The magnitude of the earthquake.
      id - The unique identifier for the earthquake.
      place - The place description of the earthquake's location.
      lineCounter - The line number in the input file where this earthquake's data was read.

      public String toString()
      Returns a string representation of the classified earthquake, including its attributes and magnitude classification.
      Overrides:
      toString in class Earthquake
      Returns:

    • getMagnitudeClass

      public String getMagnitudeClass()
      Determines the magnitude classification of the earthquake based on its magnitude.
      Returns:
      "Major" if magnitude is greater than or equal to 7.0, "Moderate" if magnitude is greater than or equal to 5.0, or "Minor" otherwise.
